  <title class="- topic/title ">New or Returning Visitor</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Each visitor is counted as either a new
	 or returning visitor. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p> A visitor is included in the "Visitor: New" segment if it is the
		visitor's first time visiting the site, the first time since clearing cookies,
		the first time since the 
		<filepath>mbox.js</filepath> file was installed, or if it has been two
		weeks since the last visit. (For information about extending the two-week
		profile lifetime, see 
		<xref href="c_visitor_profile_lifetime.xml#concept_D9F21B416F1F49159F03036BA2DD54FD" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Visitor Profile Lifetime?></xref>.)
		
	 </p>
    <p> The visitor is included in the "Visitor: Returning" segment if the user
		previously visited the site, left for at least 30 minutes, and returned to the
		site again with the same cookies. As long as a visitor returns within 14 days,
		they will be a returning visitor. 
	 </p>
    <p>The count of users in the new segment and return segment do not always
		add up to the total number of visitors. A visitor can be counted as new, then
		return and get counted as a return visitor. That visitor is still counted as
		only a single visitor in the visitor count. 
	 </p>
